-- UBS Names Sharkey, Fitzgibbon Heads of Australia Capital Markets
-- B y   B r e t t   F o l e y
-- 2012-02-24T03:31:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-24/ubs-names-sharkey-fitzgibbon-heads-of-australia-capital-markets.html
UBS AG (UBSN) , Switzerland’s biggest bank,
named Barry Sharkey and Dane Fitzgibbon co-heads of its
Australian  capital markets  unit.  Robbie Vanderzeil, based in Sydney, will oversee global
capital markets for the local executive management team,
according to a memo obtained by Bloomberg News. Andrew Defina,
Simon Cox and Fergus Blackstock will continue in their roles as
heads of equity origination, syndication and debt origination
respectively, according to the memo.  A UBS spokeswoman confirmed the memo’s contents.  Andrew Stevens, a Melbourne-based equity capital markets
banker, is taking sabbatical after 17 years with the firm,
according to the memo. Sarah Rennie, also from the capital
markets unit, will also leave, according to the memo.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brett Foley in Melbourne at 
